# MACU Studio machine config.
#
# Copy to `.env` on a NEW machine (e.g. Leo) and adjust the storage root. On Max,
# leave NO `.env` here — every value defaults to the current Max literal, so Max
# runs identically with no .env present. `.env` is gitignored; this file is tracked.
#
# Loaded by studio/backend/macu_studio/config.py and pipeline/lib.py (python-dotenv).
# python-dotenv does NOT override vars already set in the environment, so systemd
# Environment=/EnvironmentFile= lines still win.

# ---- Storage root — usually the ONLY thing you change per machine ----
MACU_SHARES=/mnt/storage/shares/MACU
# Derived from MACU_SHARES by default; override only if these live off that tree:
# MACU_EPISODES=/mnt/storage/shares/MACU/episodes
# MACU_ASSETS=/mnt/storage/shares/MACU/assets
# MACU_PIPELINE=/mnt/storage/shares/MACU/pipeline

# ---- ComfyUI output (where the render server picks up webps) ----
MACU_COMFY_OUT=/mnt/storage/comfyui/output/macu
MACU_COMFY_OUTPUT_ROOT=/mnt/storage/comfyui/output

# ---- audio-gen (agen) CLI location ----
MACU_AGEN=/mnt/storage/audio-gen/agen

# ---- Local service endpoints (loopback; change only if a service is remote) ----
# MACU_COMFY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
# MACU_PIPER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5050
# MACU_OMNIVOICE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3900
# MACU_OMNIVOICE_CONTAINER=omnivoice
# MACU_RENDER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8773

# ---- Render service (serve.py :8773) ----
# MACU_RENDER_JOBS=                         # per-job state dir; default /var/lib/macu-render/jobs
#                                           # if writable, else ~/.local/state/macu-render/jobs
# MACU_WHISPER_VENV=                        # python with faster-whisper; default <repo>/.whisper-venv

# ---- Node / hyperframes (title cards) ----
# MACU_NPX=                                 # path to npx; default = whatever's on PATH
# MACU_NODE_BIN=                            # node bin dir to prepend to PATH (e.g. an nvm dir)

# ---- Episode versioning (git-sync) ----
# Episode text is versioned in a SEPARATE content git repo (not the code repo), so a
# clone of the code ships none of your episodes. Defaults to episode_meta/ (auto
# `git init`ed, local-only). To back it up: `cd episode_meta && git remote add origin <url>`.
# MACU_CONTENT_REPO=                        # default <repo>/episode_meta
# MACU_CONTENT_REMOTE_REF=origin/main       # ref the sync dot compares against

# ---- Studio bind ----
# Studio has NO authentication. It binds 127.0.0.1 (this machine only) by default.
# Set 0.0.0.0 ONLY to reach it from another device on a network you trust — doing so
# hands every write/render endpoint to anyone on that network.
# MACU_STUDIO_HOST=127.0.0.1
# MACU_STUDIO_PORT=8774

# ---- Studio chat tile / writers-room bridge ----
# MACU_CHAT_CHANNEL_URL=http://localhost:8802/   # where Studio POSTs chat messages
# MACU_CHAT_REPLY_URL=                            # default http://localhost:<port>/api/chat/reply
# MACU_CHAT_BRIDGE_PORT=8802
# MACU_CHAT_BRIDGE_ALLOW_NO_AUTH=                 # 1 = run the bridge without a token (trusted LAN)
# MACU_CLAUDE_ALLOWED_TOOLS=                      # optional --allowedTools allowlist for the bridge
# MACU_CLAUDE_PERMISSION_MODE=                    # optional --permission-mode for the bridge

# ---- Misc ----
# MACU_STORAGE_MOUNT=/mnt/storage           # disk-usage widget mount (cosmetic)
# STACKCHAN_URL=                            # optional LED progress device; unset = disabled
# MACU_NO_STACKCHAN=1                       # force-disable the StackChan LED calls
# MACU_KEEP_OMNIVOICE=1                     # leave OmniVoice running between renders

# ---- Secrets / integrations (optional; prefer ~/.claude/... and ~/.config/... files) ----
# SS_CHAT_WEBHOOK_TOKEN=
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY=
# YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID=
